I’m that project kid that dodged the needle vials
Thanks for the pressure
Ya clowns made a diamond
I was meant to be here
It’s all about the timing

Where was you when I went homeless for this rap shit?
Three kids and little brother and my Queen
You either love me or hate me
There’s nothing in between
They say blood is thicker than
I beg the differ
You need that water to cleanse that blood when shit gets thicker
I'm in that nose bleed section
I bet you’re wondering now
You never build me up
So you can’t bring me down
The moments of clarity will purify the blurry line
Double up
I’m point like Curry at the line
It’s me against world until they take my hours from me and put them follows on me and say he empowered homies
